Mountain Protocol, which was licensed by the Bermuda Monetary Authority as a digital asset issuer on July 27,&nbsp; is <a href="https://mountainprotocol.notion.site/The-First-Regulated-Permissionless-Yield-Bearing-Stablecoin-USDM-47a7914fbe6e427d88c4084782576d88" data-v-f87c67ca="">launching</a> what it says is the first nationally-regulated, yield-bearing stablecoin called USDM.<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
The ERC-20 token was designed to give non-U.S. users access to U.S. Treasury yields and can be used across a myriad DeFi protocols, Mountain Protocol wrote in a Monday in a social media <a href="https://twitter.com/MountainUSDM/status/1701208170931081576" data-v-f87c67ca="">thread</a>.&nbsp;
